{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"355e00d9-c0eb-47e9-8c9f-4754d9513289","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0+ dropped VSTest as the default runner.** Starting with v4.0.0, `MSTest.Sdk` defaults to **Microsoft Testing Platform** (the newer runner) and no longer ships the VSTest adapter. That's why `vstest.console` can't discover your tests — there's no VSTest adapter in the output anymore.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 — Switch your CI to the new runner\nRun tests directly via:\n```\ndotnet test\n```\nor invoke the test executable directly. No project changes needed.\n\n### Option 2 — Re-enable VSTest compatibility\nAdd this property to your project:\n\n```xml\n<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n```\n\nThis brings back the VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` works again.\n\n---\n\nWant me to apply either fix to your `TestProject.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"89b14c19-726d-48c4-b2de-73f870fc204c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a well-known breaking change in MSTest SDK. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (the new `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`). This means that `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests by default because the VSTest adapter/infrastructure is no longer included.\n\nLet me explain this clearly.","outputTokens":340,"requestId":"E3EE:E9D27:240D3D6:2809B94:6A054023"},"id":"7ec6b644-c071-4326-831a-57d43e076cc1","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:23:25.412Z","parentId":"41fb8dda-86f2-4cbe-8b36-3bae67f787d7"}
